    {
        "url": "/quotes/floyd_skloot_738578",
        "quote": "A risk for a poet-novelist is imbalance: The poems can flatten into prose or lose their intensity of focus; the novels can stall amid lofty writing or literary preciousness and ignore the engine of plot and character.",
