    {
        "url": "/quotes/floyd_skloot_738572",
        "quote": "I'm a writer who simply can't know what I'm writing about until the writing lets me discover it. In a sense, my writing process embraces the gapped nature of my memory process, leaping across spaces that represent all I've lost and establishing fresh patterns within all that remains.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Floyd Skloot",
            "url": "/quotes/floyd_skloot_738572"
